        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 29 at 11:49PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 1148 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 6
miles west of Lela, or 11 miles west of Shamrock, moving northeast at
35 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lela and Shamrock.

This includes Interstate 40 between mile markers 143 and 168.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
